“Dear future self,

I wish you moved more.

I wish you took your health more seriously.

I wish you spent more time challenging yourself.

I wish you were more willing to try new things.

Because I know you’ll be paying for it…

…in your body, mind, career, relationship or as a parent.”

👇🏾

You know what’s crazy about this letter?!

It applies to so many people because guess what…

It’s happening 🤷‍♂️🤯

37% of people don’t exercise and only 13% say that they exercise ‘regularly’ 🤯

NEARLY HALF OF THE POPULATION! 🙈

I know I’m a huge advocate of resistance training, but I’d be happy if the other 63% simply hit their steps! 💃

I know for a fact that if you make a conscious effort to exercise, it will positively influence many other areas of your life without your even realising.

That one session can change everything!

Imagine what you could do with all this new found energy and confidence… 

Maybe you will do that one thing you keep putting off?

Then all of a sudden you’re meeting likeminded people…

Pushing yourself like you never have before…

Finding purpose & fulfilment…

But it all starts with YOU taking action 😉

It’s not to late.

Comment below if you needed to hear this today 🙌🏾

My best piece of advice?

Do what makes you better, not what’s easy.

When you do what makes you better, what was once hard, becomes easy.

When you repeat this process over and over, you will get addicted to embracing discomfort at any opportunity.

If you lack consistency with your health, mind or food…

You don’t value it enough.

Or

You haven’t associated how being healthier with more energy and a stronger body, will improve you in the areas of your life you value most.

The truth is, you will never value what you haven’t had to work for.

Instead you’ll find yourself being complacent and inconsistent. 

I challenge you to push yourself harder, move your body more and eat healthier for just one week, then tell me how much better you look and feel.

It’s time for you to drop the excuses.

For one reason or another, I know we’ve all been there. You might be there right now. Your reasons could be your busy lifestyle or you’re just prioritising everyone else. It’s completely normal… but staying there is a choice.

If you can’t be the best version of yourself, everything around you will feel the impact. The people you love, your friendships, your business and most importantly… You!

6 TIPS to stay in optimal shape year round without having to compromise your lifestyle…

🧠 Remind yourself why you need to be in great shape everyday… when you are aware of WHO needs you to be healthy, you will be DISCIPLINED to implement the habits and actions that create it 👊🏾

📝 SCHEDULE your weekly exercise like a business appointment to yourself - the time you invest will buy you back greater productivity, more confidence and higher energy

❌ You don’t need to diet. Instead FORWARD PLAN what you will eat ahead of time. Don’t get caught off guard.

🥦 90% of your food needs to be HIGH QUALITY REAL FOOD everyday, year round. Avoid refined sugar and processed food as much as you can. Nothing will help you feel better than controlling these two things.

🛌 SLEEP 7 hours minimum every night. When you sleep better, you train harder, recover better, eat healthier and perform better across the board.

👫 I spend my time and attention with PEOPLE who VALUE HEALTH - through partner, friends, clients, team. Nothing shapes habits and sets standards more.

BONUS TIP - NEVER B/S YOURSELF.

You will never re-negotiate your health, when you have a deeper meaning attached to it.

I am yet to coach a person who doesn’t have a lot on every week. You’re busy, I get it. We all are.

It’s not an excuse to not stay healthy and to want to be better.

We are almost 5 months into the year. My clients and I are primed and ready to continue working hard and setting new standards with our body, mind and health.

If you want to be a cut above “the norm” and want my help to guide you there, drop me a message 🎯

Want to know a secret?

I’ve slipped up on my “diet” this month.

Not just once, but multiple times

And guess what?

I know I’ll slip up again and again.

So why haven’t I spiralled out of control? Or thrown the head up and stopped? Or tried something different? 🤔 

It’s called language and mindset! 🧠 

When I over eat I don’t call it a binge… and I sure as hell don’t make it a game of how bad can I be… 😂

I get over it and get right back on track the next day.

There isn’t a single person reading this that doesn’t veer off track on occasion!

The good news is you don’t need to be perfect to lose body fat and build a healthy, lean body.

What it takes is consistency.

Maybe yesterday wasn’t your best day. 

Maybe the whole weekend was a write off.

The best thing you can do is move on from it and the next time you slip up (because you will) don’t make it as bad as this one.

Acknowledge it, accept it, understand it’s not a big deal and get back on track ASAP.

Consistency beats perfection, every single time.

#AamirFit #FatLoss #Weightloss #Transformation #OnlineCoach #Mindset

Some hard hitting facts about fitness you need to know 👇🏾

-There’s no such thing as too little. Start with something. One work out per week is wildly better than zero.

-You need sleep more than you need caffeine.

-Dynamic warm ups are better than stretching before you work out.

-You’re allowed to be the new person at the gym. We all start somewhere.

-Having protein and veg with every meal makes getting and staying lean so much easier.

-Stop drinking your calories.

-You need action, not just education. Paralysis by analysis spurs inaction. Go!

-Find something you actually like. You don’t need to join a fitness clique.

-How you look matters, but if that’s all you care about you’ll be less motivated over time. Find a deeper meaning with your fitness pursuits.

-Go when you don’t want to. That’s the secret sauce.

If you need some help getting started or simply want to start seeing some major results, drop me a DM!

1980 - works in Dubai for 18 months 
1982 - works in a 5 star hotel in Delhi
1983 - headhunted and offered a job in Belfast
1984 - takes the plunge and leaves his 7 brothers and sisters behind in India and moves to Belfast with my mum who also left her 8 brothers and sisters behind
1987- buys a house on Eglantine Avenue for 30k
1991 - opens a takeaway in Dunmurry
1992 - house in Eglantine Avenue gets set on fire (arson attack) 🙈
1994 - lives above the takeaway while he fixes the house and eventually moves back in
1998 - house gets robbed 🙈
2000 - purchases a new home and never looks back ☺️

Intrigued, I asked my dad why he took such a big risk in his 20s… 

He just smiled and said, “Son you wouldn’t have enjoyed living in Delhi quite as much as you do in Belfast” 😂 “All jokes aside, sometimes you just have to go for it, life’s too short.”

What a man! I’d be lost without him (literally 🤣)

What’s my why?

Simply put, my family deserves me at my best…

I work out so I can have more energy, which ensures I’m more present and able to enjoy every moment we spend together. 

Let your children see you take care of yourself. Then show them how.

I’m not just talking about exercise, I’m talking about overall lifestyle practices. Resting, cooking, cleaning, managing stress, setting boundaries.

Part of showing love to your child is making sure you’re fit and healthy. Another part is setting an example.

Carving out time to take care of yourself isn’t selfish ☺️
